ctPriorityExtTXQueueTable.name: ctPriorityExtTXQueueTable
ctPriorityExtTXQueueTable.description: This table provides information pertaining to the number of physical transmit queues per interface.

ctPriorityExtTXQueueEntry.name: ctPriorityExtTXQueueEntry
ctPriorityExtTXQueueEntry.description: Specifies the number of transmit queues for this interface.

ctPriorityExtSlotNum.name: ctPriorityExtSlotNum
ctPriorityExtSlotNum.description: The slot num of the device that the interface is located on.

ctPriorityExtInterfaceNum.name: ctPriorityExtInterfaceNum

ctPriorityExtNumTXQueues.name: ctPriorityExtNumTXQueues

ctPriorityExtMACStatus.name: ctPriorityExtMACStatus
ctPriorityExtMACStatus.description: Defines the status of the priority packet forwarding based on MAC address. Setting ctIfPriorityExtMACStatus to a value of disable(2), disables the forwarding of packets based on priority table information. All information remains in existence but is not considered in the forwarding decision.

ctPriorityExtNumMACEntries.name: ctPriorityExtNumMACEntries
ctPriorityExtNumMACEntries.description: The number of active entries in the ctPriorityExtMACTable.

ctPriorityExtMaxNumMACEntries.name: ctPriorityExtMaxNumMACEntries
ctPriorityExtMaxNumMACEntries.description: The maximum number of entries allowed in the ctPriorityExtMACTable.

ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypesPerMACEntry.name: ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypesPerMACEntry
ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypesPerMACEntry.description: The maximum number of packet types that can be asssociated with any one MAC address in the ctPriorityExtMACTable

ctPriorityExtMACTable.name: ctPriorityExtMACTable
ctPriorityExtMACTable.description: This table provides the ability to specify priority based on the MAC addresses encoded in a packet. There are several possible permutations achieveable via this table. Priorities in this table may be based on the following criteria: Destination address and specific packet type and VLAN ID Destination address and specific packet type Destination address Source address and specific packet type and VLAN ID Source address and specific packet type Source address Destination or source address and specific packet type and VLAN ID Destination or source address and specific packet type Destination or source address Depending on the values set in the table which of these criteria will be used for any given packet. If any given relationship can not be created the set will fail with a BAD-VALUE error.

ctPriorityExtMACEntry.name: ctPriorityExtMACEntry
ctPriorityExtMACEntry.description: Describes a particular MAC address priority entry.

ctPriorityExtMACAddr.name: ctPriorityExtMACAddr
ctPriorityExtMACAddr.description: The MAC address which will have a priority associated with it as specified by ctPriorityExtMACPriority.

ctPriorityExtAddrType.name: ctPriorityExtAddrType
ctPriorityExtAddrType.description: The type of MAC address which will have priority associated with it as specified by ctPriorityExtMACPriority.

ctPriorityExtMACPktType.name: ctPriorityExtMACPktType
ctPriorityExtMACPktType.description: The packet type associated with a particular MAC address, specified by ctPriorityExtMACAddr, which will have priority associated with it as specified by ctPriorityExtMACPriority. A value of 1 indicates that this entry pertains to all packet types. A single value in the range of 0x0600..0xFFFF indicates that this entry only pertains to that particular packet type.

ctPriorityExtMACVlanId.name: ctPriorityExtMACVlanId
ctPriorityExtMACVlanId.description: A set of 65335 (0xFFFF) causes the priority value specified in ctPriorityExtMACPriority to apply to all packets matching the criteria specified by ctPriorityExtMACAddr, ctPriorityExtAddrType, and ctPriorityExtMACPktType. Any value between 1 and 4095 is a valid VLAN ID (IEEE 802.1q) and causes ctPriorityExtMACPriority to only apply to packets that are of matching the above criteria and that are members of the IEEE 802.1q VLAN specified by the value set.

ctPriorityExtMACPriority.name: ctPriorityExtMACPriority
ctPriorityExtMACPriority.description: A set of delete(100) will delete this row from the ctPriorityExtMACTable. A set of priority(1-8) will either create a row in the ctPriorityExtMACTable with the specified priority or modify an existing entry with the newly specified priority.

ctPriorityExtPktTypeStatus.name: ctPriorityExtPktTypeStatus
ctPriorityExtPktTypeStatus.description: Defines the status of the priority packet forwarding based exclusively on packet type. Setting ctIfPriorityPktTypeExtStatus to a value of disable(2) disables the forwarding of packets based on priority table information. All information remains in existence but is not considered in the forwarding decision.

ctPriorityExtNumPktTypeEntries.name: ctPriorityExtNumPktTypeEntries
ctPriorityExtNumPktTypeEntries.description: The number of active entries in the ctPriorityExtPktTypeTable.

ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypeEntries.name: ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypeEntries
ctPriorityExtMaxNumPktTypeEntries.description: The maximum number of entries allowed in the ctPriorityExtPktTypeTable.

ctPriorityExtPktTypeTable.name: ctPriorityExtPktTypeTable
ctPriorityExtPktTypeTable.description: This table provides the ability to specify priority based on the packet type encoded in a packet. Priorities in this table may be based on the following criteria: Packet type and VLAN ID Packet type If any given relationship can not be created the set will fail with a BAD-VALUE error.

ctPriorityExtPktTypeEntry.name: ctPriorityExtPktTypeEntry
ctPriorityExtPktTypeEntry.description: Describes a particular packet type priority entry.

ctPriorityExtPktType.name: ctPriorityExtPktType
ctPriorityExtPktType.description: The packet type which will have priority associated with it as specified by ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority. A value of 1 indicates that this entry pertains to all packet types. A single value in the range of 0x0600..0xFFFF indicates that this entry only pertains to that particular packet type.

ctPriorityExtPktTypeVlanId.name: ctPriorityExtPktTypeVlanId
ctPriorityExtPktTypeVlanId.description: A set of 65535 (0xFFFF) causes the priority value specified in ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority to apply to all packets of the type specified by ctPriorityExtPktType. Any value between 1 and 4095 is a valid VLAN ID (IEEE 802.1q) and causes ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority to only apply to packets that are of ctPriorityExtPktType type and are members of the IEEE 802.1q VLAN specified by the value set.

ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority.name: ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority
ctPriorityExtPktTypePriority.description: A set of delete(100) will delete this row from the ctPriorityExtPriorityTypeTable. A set of priority(1-8) will either create a row in the ctPriorityExtPriorityTypeTable with the specified priority or modify an existing entry with the newly specified priority.

ctPriorityExtPortStatus.name: ctPriorityExtPortStatus
ctPriorityExtPortStatus.description: Defines the status of the priority packet forwarding based on receive port. Setting ctIfPriorityExtPortStatus to a value of disable(2), disables the forwarding of packets based on priority table information. All information remains in existence but is not considered in the forwarding decision.

ctPriorityExtPortTable.name: ctPriorityExtPortTable
ctPriorityExtPortTable.description: This table provides information pertaining to the priority associated with a receive port.

ctPriorityExtPortEntry.name: ctPriorityExtPortEntry
ctPriorityExtPortEntry.description: Specifies the priority associated with a specific physical interface.

ctPriorityExtPortSlotNum.name: ctPriorityExtPortSlotNum
ctPriorityExtPortSlotNum.description: The slot num of the device that the interface is located on.

ctPriorityExtPortInterfaceNum.name: ctPriorityExtPortInterfaceNum
ctPriorityExtPortInterfaceNum.description: The interface number for which the information is requested.

ctPriorityExtPortPriority.name: ctPriorityExtPortPriority
ctPriorityExtPortPriority.description: A set of priority(1-8) will modify an existing entry with the newly specified priority. Entries cannot be deleted from this table.

ctPriorityExtFwdInboundPriority.name: ctPriorityExtFwdInboundPriority
ctPriorityExtFwdInboundPriority.description: This controls whether a packet that is received with a priority tag is forwarded with the priority encoded in the tag or the default priority of the port. A value of enable(1) means the packet will be forwarded with the priority encoded in the tag. A value of disable(2) means the packet will be given the default priority of the port it was received on.
